comments: Hardaway Jr. (DAL) lightly brushes Holiday's (MIL) side and the contact during the drive is marginal.
Holiday (MIL) establishes himself in Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs as the two come together during the pick.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) legally contests Middleton's (MIL) jump shot attempt.
Kleber (DAL) and Lopez (MIL) engage and disengage in the paint and the contact during the rebounding opportunity is marginal.
Middleton (MIL) moves alongside Doncic's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs during the drive.
Doncic (DAL) gathers the ball on his left foot and takes two legal steps  before releasing his pass.
Middleton (MIL) moves to Doncic's (DAL) space and marginal contact occurs as Doncic receives the post entry pass.
Doncic (DAL) brings his right arm down towards his side and marginal contact occurs with Middleton's (MIL) bracing forearm in the post.
Lopez (MIL) legally contests Doncic's (DAL) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Allen (MIL) and Finney-Smith (DAL) engage and disengage during the rebounding opportunity and the contact is marginal.
Lopez (MIL) and Kleber (DAL) engage and disengage away from the ball and the contact is marginal.

Lopez (MIL) establishes himself in Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and Lopez's arms come out slightly as he releases away from the defender and rolls towards the basket. The contact on the play is marginal.
Dinwiddie (DAL) is the last player to touch the ball prior to it careening out of bounds. Possession is properly retained by Milwaukee.
Hill (MIL) establishes himself in Finney-Smith's (DAL) path and the defender avoids contact as he maneuvers around the screen.
Finney-Smith (DAL) gets to ball height and blocks Middleton's (MIL) jump shot attempt. The arm contact after the contact with the ball is considered incidental.
The shot clock expires before Milwaukee is able to attempt a shot that  makes contact with the rim. Possession is properly conferred to Dallas.

Holiday (MIL) reaches in for the ball and his arm grazes Doncic's (DAL) chin and the contact is marginal. Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Hardaway Jr. (DAL) establishes himself in Holiday's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs as Holiday fights over the pick.
Kleber (DAL) establishes himself in Holiday's (MIL) path and marginal contact occurs as the two players come together during the pick.
Holiday (MIL) and Kleber (DAL) engage and disengage as Kleber rolls into the paint and the contact is marginal.
Doncic (DAL) brings his left hand underneath the ball, bringing his live dribble to a brief pause.
Lopez (MIL) places an arm against Doncic's (DAL) back and the contact during his driving shot attempt is marginal.
Kleber (DAL) comes together with Lopez (MIL) as Lopez sets the pick and the contact is marginal.
Finney-Smith (DAL) and Lopez (MIL) engage and disengage as Lopez rolls into the post and the contact is marginal.
Kleber (DAL) legally contests Middleton's (MIL) perimeter jump shot attempt.
Lopez (MIL) makes last contact with the ball prior to it going out of bounds. Possession is properly awarded to Dallas.
Middleton (MIL) slides his left arm off of Kleber's (DAL) back and the contact during the inbounds pass is marginal.
Finney-Smith (DAL) does not fully reestablish himself in the court of play before coming into contact with the ball. Possession should have been awarded to Milwaukee.
Middleton (MIL) moves into Finney-Smith's (DAL) space and initiates body contact that affects his SQBR while in possession of the ball.
Lopez (MIL) clamps and holds Kleber's (DAL) left arm during the rebound and the contact impairs Kleber's range of motion during the rebounding opportunity.
Middleton (MIL) establishes himself in Kleber's (DAL) path and marginal contact occurs as the two player's come together during the screen.
Holiday (MIL) reaches in for the ball and deflects it away from Doncic (DAL) during his spin-dribble.
Middleton (MIL) and Wood (DAL) come together after the screen and marginal contact occurs as the players engage and disengage.
Holiday (MIL) avoids making contact with Doncic's (DAL) arm and legally contests Doncic's perimeter jump shot attempt.
